		<div class="post" id="post-4045548">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4045548)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4045548">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=348648&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164195" alt="sirpudding" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=348648)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;" >sirpudding</a></span> <span class="odate time_1540989928 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">31 Oct 2018 12:45</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4045548">
									

<p>Upvoted mainly for presentation, rather than content, and I suppose also because when people on reddit insist on the &quot;canonicity&quot; of this event, they will at least link here instead of some random unpublished low quality knockoff of the 682 termination log sandboxed draft.</p>
<p>I think there's some good parts here, Daniels is at least marginally developed as a character, and the denouement had a good feel of sloppy verisimilitude about it.</p>
<p>Where this fails, is that I don't think that I really care if 096 was ever terminated or not and this doesn't really make much effort to sell it to me. I don't especially find the object itself very compelling, I don't have any interest in using it for anything<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-561854-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-561854-1')">1</a></sup>, and I am content to imagine that any given Foundation either doesn't have one, neutralized it years ago without fanfare, or has it Euclid contained without further incident.</p>
<p>Which just means that I wasn't the target audience for this.</p>
<p>This does present a bit of a continuity conundrum, in that it's hard to imagine why the Foundation cares about destroying this one particular thing (which is pretty solidly contained in total darkness now) when they seem committed to unstable Keter containment of many worse ones, but that's probably just a hobgoblin of small minds.</p>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-561854-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-561854-1')">1</a>. Except, goddammit, I of course just thought of an idea, for an <em>origin story</em> of all things. Brains, whatcha gonna do, amirite?</div>
</div>

							</div>

								
